rComments: A very disorganized class and professor.
He's very subjective.. if he likes you, he'll give you a better mark, else.. might as well not take the course.  No clear criteria on marking either.

He's an okay prof. Midterm was easy but watch out for the final. I think he fixes the grades. Everyone will end up in the B- range. Don't take this course if you expect A- or higher because he doesn't give them. It's very rare that anyone gets above B+.

There is tons of reading in the class notes pkg.  As long as you read & mass memorize EVERYTHING in the notes package, you'll do extremely well!  Midterm & final exams are VERY straightforward if you memorized the info.  The case assign. is a lot of work, but fair.  How he comes up with the (final) marks is a mystery and tricky.

Doesn't teach much - 90% of class time is "debates" amoung students. Focused too much on Government ethics instead of business ethics (he works for the gov't maybe that's why?) Not neutral enough on certain issues, it shows during debates. Exam was CRAZYY with 3-4 LONGGG case to read THEN with abcdefg parts to answer..overall didn't like this calss
